\fs64 \
\

\fs52 3 cups old fashioned oats\
1 1/2 cups nuts (pistachios)\
1/2 to 3/4 cup maple syrup\
1 T. brown sugar\
1/2 cup canola oil\
1 t. kosher salt (3/4 t. regular salt)\
2 cups seed (pumpkin, sunflower and sesame)\
1 cup big unsweetened coconut flakes or chips\
1 cup dried fruit (dried apricots, craisins)\
1/2 t. cardamom\
1/4 t. nutmeg  \
1/4 t. ginger\
1 cup M and M's\
1 egg white\
\

\fs54 Measure grain, nuts, seeds, salt, and spices into a large bowl.\
Add sweeteners, oil, and egg white.\
Stir, stir, stir.\
Spread out and pat the granola into an even layer on a large Silpat lined baking sheet.\
Bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes or more.\
Stop when the granola looks toasty brown and smells incredible.\
Let the granola cool completely in the pan, then store in an airtight container. 
